Description:   Clinical Operations Director (Permanent) - New Hope, PA

Job Search Options

&amp;amp;gt; Apply to this Job! &amp;amp;gt; Tell a Friend! &amp;amp;gt; Back to Search Results &amp;amp;gt; Start a New Search

Current Search Criteria Keywords:  Locations: ANY Category: ANY Job Code: 423317 Job Location: New Hope, PA Category: Clinical Study Manager Last Updated: 10/18/2007 A biotechnology company engaged in the development of a new class of drugs for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis, idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura and a host of other autoimmune disorders.

POSITION:

Clinical Operations Director will be responsible for the implementation of Phase Ib/IIa rheumatology clinical trials to be conducted mainly ex-U.S sites. This position will be required to manage and coordinate all clinical trial activities with clinical research organization, data management, biostatistician, central laboratory, and third party consultants for a multi-center clinical trial. This position will be responsible for all administrative duties necessary for strategic planning, project management, timelines, budgets and day-to-day communications required for clinical trial management.

FUNCTIONAL RESPONSIBILITIES:

.     Lead manager of the assigned protocol(s); planning, organizing, communicating and implementing study objectives for assigned protocol(s).

.     Actively participates in clinical team meetings; lead discussion on assigned protocol(s). Brief senior management on strategic, operational, and financial issues relative to assigned programs.

.     Communicate effectively with members of the extended project team(s).

.     Prepares or delegates and supervises preparation of protocol, amendments, CRF, informed consent form, operations manual, and other documentation required for conduct of a clinical trial.

.     Assists with the preparation of required regulatory documents, such as IDE/PMA annual reports, updating of the IB, and final study reports for assigned protocol(s).

.     Manages the day-to-day clinical operations of assigned protocol(s); including management of vendors (e.g. CRO, central lab) and coordination of team member activities.

.     Develop draft study budgets, with Medical Director

.     Conduct and/or review qualification visits to vendors when required.

.     Actively participate in the conduct of investigator meetings including advance preparation, presentations, problem resolution and follow-up.

.     Support CRO CRAs on all aspects of monitoring, to resolve difficult study issues at sites.

.     Arrange Audit study sites when needed to ensure monitoring compliance by CRO.

.     Review monitoring and initiaition reports submitted by CROs

.     With regulatory affairs, arrange regulatory file audits if needed to ensure compliance with all applicable regulatory authorities.

.     Take lead role, in coordinations with contracted CROs, for development of comprehensive subject recruitment strategy and monitor enrollment to assure milestones are met.

.     Identify, analyze, and report any serious compliance issues, and develop action plan for approval by management. May require monitoring visits to resolve difficult study conduct issues.

.     Coordinate and plan with Project Manager for Clinical Supply Chain to ensure continual availability, of clinical and non-clinical supplies necessary to meet study requirements.

.     Review tables, listings, and study reports for assigned protocol(s).

.     Understand roles and relationships of all relevant functional areas in the extended project team, in order to proactively identify and contribute to the resolution of issue affecting the multi-disciplinary team.

.     Anticipate study conduct issues and assist in developing contingency plans prior to study initiation.

.     Represent clinical trial and company at various indication-related meetings.

.     Travel approximately 25%

Skills / EXPERIENCE:

The Clinical Operations Director should have a minimum of 10+ years experience in the pharmaceutical industry, with 6+ years clinical trial managing experience. The candidate must understand pharmaceutical clinical development processes and should have significant experience with responsible roles in the conduct or management of phase I and II clinical trials.

The candidate must have a B.A./B.S. degree or equivalent, MS or PhD preferred; a health science degree or biologic science degree is preferred. The candidate must have a good working knowledge of medical terminology, physiology and pharmacology and an excellent knowledge of applicable U.S. and international regulations and guidelines. Candidate should place the highest priority on the ethical and safe conduct of clinical research.

Please refer to Job code soliant-423317 when responding to this ad.

